<figureCitation id="9DE82A35FFE7FFAA1C62BB67A989876C" box="[570,641,1876,1902]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 5" captionStartId="7.[264,382,1004,1028]" captionTargetBox="[418,1160,325,975]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[409,1177,304,994]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 5. Details of Hemiosus selva Short, sp. n. (3, 5) and H. exilis (LeConte) (4). 3 – 4: pronotal coloration, scale bar 0.18 mm; 5: aedeagus, scale bar 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/174868/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number id="B31B2497FFE7FFAA1C29BB67A989876C" box="[625,641,1876,1902]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
) serve to distinguish this species in Mesoamerica.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
